--- !u!114 &1083053942
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1083053941}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ff41284d8a1c8b0498218d8f11cc6984, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::DialogueTrigger
  startingNode:
    dialogue:
    - Good evening.
    - I wanted to thank you for your hospitality in allowing me to stay temporarily.
    - How long do you think this flood will last?
    choices:
    - choiceText: Hopefully not long
      nextNode:
        dialogue:
        - I wouldn't be too upset if it lasted a bit longer...
        choices:
        - choiceText: Why?
          nextNode:
            dialogue:
            - Erm...
            - Well, I don't have anyone to talk to so...
            - I appreciate that you let me stay with you and talk with you.
            - Truly, thank you.
            choices: []
        - choiceText: I would
          nextNode:
            dialogue:
            - Ah, yes...
            - Silly me, I suppose it wouldn't be ideal.
            - I apologise for my rudeness.
            choices: []
    - choiceText: I have no idea
      nextNode:
        dialogue:
        - Yes I guess you wouldn't...
        - So... erm...
        - What do you do for work?
        choices:
        - choiceText: 'Nurse '
          nextNode:
            dialogue:
            - Ah, really?
            - My wife was a nurse.
            - And a damn good one too... heh.
            choices: []
        - choiceText: Teacher
          nextNode:
            dialogue:
            - Ah, really?
            - My daughter is a teacher.
            - I hope she's doing well...
            choices: []
